OL,6,FThe all-party inquiry, led by the
OL,7,FConservative MP, Theo Clarke, and
OL,8,FLabour's Rosie Duffield, looked into
OL,9,Fthe causes behind traumatic births.
OL,11,FClarke was inspired to take action
OL,12,Fafter needing emergency surgery and
OL,13,Fthinking she was going to die after
OL,14,Fthe birth of her daughter in 2022.
OL,16,FThe parliamentary inquiry's aim is to
OL,17,Fdevelop policy recommendations to
OL,18,Freduce the rate of birth-related
OL,19,Ftrauma.
