OL,3,CMum-of-three tried to take her own
OL,4,Clife after traumatic birth
OL,6,FIt included women whose babies have
OL,7,Fdied or suffered permanent brain
OL,8,Fdamage, as a result of mistakes made
OL,9,Fduring birth, as well as women who
OL,10,Fhave experienced physical injuries
OL,11,Fthat have left them with bladder and
OL,12,Fbowel incontinence.
OL,14,FDr Kim Thomas, CEO of the Birth Trauma
OL,15,FAssociation, who wrote the report,
OL,16,Fsaid she had been shocked by the
OL,17,Fstories submitted by parents:
OL,18,F"Hundreds of women told us that their
OL,19,Flives had been ruined by their
OL,20,Fexperience of birth: the word 'broken'
OL,21,Fcame up frequently.
