OL,3,CMum-of-three tried to take her own
OL,4,Clife after traumatic birth
OL,6,F"Many told us that they could no
OL,7,Flonger work because of the injury they
OL,8,Fsustained, whether that was a physical
OL,9,Finjury, such as a severe tear causing
OL,10,Flong-term incontinence, or a
OL,11,Fpsychological injury, leaving women
OL,12,Fwith post-traumatic stress disorder.
OL,14,F"They also told us that the trauma had
OL,15,Faffected their ability to bond with
OL,16,Ftheir baby, their relationship with
OL,17,Ftheir partner and even their
OL,18,Frelationship with family and friends.
OL,19,FThe lack of understanding from others
OL,20,Fmeant that these women often felt
OL,21,Fextremely isolated."
