OL,6,FOne of the most upsetting elements of
OL,7,Fthe stories, Dr Thomas said, was that
OL,8,Fso many women felt that they had not
OL,9,Fbeen listened to.
OL,11,F"Many women we heard from had told
OL,12,Fmaternity professionals that they were
OL,13,Fconcerned that something had gone
OL,14,Fwrong in labour, only to be dismissed
OL,15,Fas being over-anxious," she said.
OL,17,F"This failure to listen to women then
OL,18,Fresulted in catastrophic outcomes,
OL,19,Fsuch as a baby being stillborn."
